This repository contains original governance artifacts (custom guardrail rules,
OPA firewall allowlist, configuration, integration entrypoints, Kubernetes
manifests, dashboard, and the agent system prompt) that build on the following
third-party projects. Those projects are NOT redistributed here — this repo only
references and configures them. Each retains its own license and copyright.

- Cisco DefenseClaw (Cisco AI Defense)
  License: Apache-2.0
  Runtime guardrails, OPA policy engine, admission scanning, and audit sinks.
  This repo's policies/ build on DefenseClaw's "strict" pack but do not include it.
  Upstream: https://github.com/cisco-ai-defense/defenseclaw

- OpenClaw
  Self-hosted agent runtime and Microsoft Teams chat surface.
  Upstream: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw

The sanitized example endpoints in this repo (Anthropic, Microsoft Bot Framework,
GitHub, npm, Cisco AI Defense, etc.) are public service endpoints referenced for
illustration of the egress allowlist; they imply no affiliation or endorsement.
